						               													<description>Guilty! is a cutthroat game of cunning, manipulation, and deceit for 3-6 adult players.  You probably want to keep children at least 500 feet away from this game at all times.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player acts as the Public Defender to one of 6 deplorable suspects being held in connection to a crime they most likely committed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It is your duty to manipulate the system at all costs to make sure that your suspect is not found guilty by playing evidence cards like &amp;quot;Brown Eyes&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Fat&amp;quot;, or &amp;quot;Mole on Face&amp;quot; and then debunk those pieces of evidence with cards like &amp;ldquo;Intimidate a Witness&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Flush the Drugs&amp;quot;, or &amp;quot;Did You Just Assume My Gender?&amp;rdquo;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Once you have pinned enough evidence on your opponents, they are found guilty and they lose.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There is no winner in Guilty, only a loser. And no one likes a loser.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;So, if you&amp;rsquo;ve ever wanted to bribe a cop, claim oppression, impersonate an officer or claim conspiracy in the comfort of your own home, Guilty! Is the game for you!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
